author: CNN
description: Authorities are still searching for a suspect after a shooting at Brown University in Providence, Rhode Island, according to campus officials. Local police say multiple people were shot but have not shared further details. Campus alerts warned students of an active shooter and urged them to remain hidden until further notice, locking doors and silencing phones.                                                                   #CNN #News
title: Authorities search for suspect after multiple people shot near Brown University, police say

title: House GOP unveils narrow health care package with key deadline looming

author: CNN
description:
President Donald Trump said Saturday that there will be “very serious retaliation” after two US soldiers and one civilian interpreter were killed in an ambush in Syria on Saturday.
Three others were wounded in the attack, which was carried out by a single ISIS gunman, US Central Command and the Department of Defense said in statements Saturday.

CNN correspondent Julia Benbrook reports from the White House, and Fredricka Whitfield speaks with CNN military analyst retired Maj. Gen. James "Spider" Marks. #CNN #News
title: Trump vows retaliation after 2 US soldiers killed in Syria attack

title: Democratic GA senator on whether it was a mistake to reopen government

description:

title: Trump blames Biden, Dems, Fed chair and immigrants for economic woes

title: Why Trump wants to oust Venezuela’s Maduro

author: CNN
description:
Democrats on the House Oversight Committee have released photos from Jeffrey Epstein’s estate Friday showing the many powerful figures in the late sex trafficker’s orbit, including President Donald Trump, former President Bill Clinton, Steve Bannon, Bill Gates, Richard Branson and others. Many of the men have been previously linked to Epstein, though the photos may shed new light on the extent of those relationships. Taken collectively, the images – which the Democrats on the committee said came from Epstein’s estate – reinforce the financier was tied in the past to a wide variety of powerful and high-profile people whose ties to him are now under significant scrutiny.

CNN's Kaitlan Collins speaks with Rep. Robert Garcia (D-CA), ranking member of the House Oversight Committee #CNN #News
title: New Epstein photos show Trump, Clinton, Gates and others

author: CNN
description: Fired University of Michigan head football coach Sherrone Moore faces charges of a felony count of home invasion and multiple misdemeanors related to his arrest on Wednesday just hours after he was dismissed. Magistrate Odetalla Odetalla entered a plea of not guilty on Moore’s behalf. The university said in a statement Wednesday that a school investigation revealed “credible evidence” that Moore was “engaged in an inappropriate relationship with a staff member.”
title: Ex-Michigan football coach pleads not guilty in court
